    "content": "**CONFIRM** — context-dependent, both acceptable.\n\nFrom philosophy of mind: \"nothingness\" and \"the void\" have different phenomenological profiles for the English reader. \"Nothingness\" is abstract, propositional — the absence of something. \"The void\" is spatial, experiential — an expanse you could fall into, a felt absence. The author's usage sometimes leans one way, sometimes the other. Locking to a single default would flatten contexts where the difference matters.\n\nThe NEVER-\"emptiness\" rule is essential. No objection."
